cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SY, cs.PF 

Reasoning: 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is the most likely category as the paper discusses the use of transport layer coding to improve streaming application performance over the Internet. 
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of coding techniques to recover from lost packets. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is another possible category as the paper specifically mentions streaming applications. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible category as the paper discusses the trade-offs between reducing delay and achieving a certain rate. 
- cs.PF (Performance) is also a possible category as the paper discusses improving application layer performance.
